ENUGU – The Federal Government has unveiled its plan to launch tradermoni in Enugu State as part of its effort to support traders in the state. This was disclosed by the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Geoffrey Onyeama, in Amagunze in Nkanu East Local Government Area of Enugu State on Tuesday during the All Progressive Congress (APC) campaign rally in the area, saying the Programme would enable traders access loan of N10, 000 and above. “We will be coming to Enugu very soon with Vice President, Yemi Osinbanjo, to launch tradermoni in order to support our people especially the women to boost their business,” he said. Onyeama, who described President Muhammadu Buhari as a visionary leader who has long-term plan for Nigeria, enjoined the people to support his re-election bid to enable him continue with the developmental projects he started since 2015 that he came into power. He said: ”Buhari has a great plan to transform Nigeria for our benefit and the benefit of our future generation.”